 for bestpractices and # Review Queue

## Overview
Develop a Review Queue page for an enterprise furniture audit platform. The page serves as a worklist for reviewers to handle low-confidence items detected by AI, exception flags, and suspicious duplicates. It supports assignment, bulk review actions, advanced filtering, and reviewer productivity metrics. The UI must be robust, accessible, and guard against runtime errors by validating and safely handling data at all points. The implementation must strictly follow the runtime safety rules provided (null/undefined guards, proper useState initialization, and safe array operations).

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Review Queue is a centralized worklist for reviewers to Manage AI-detected items needing human validation. It surfaces three primary item categories: Low Confidence items, Exceptions, and Duplicates, plus an “Assigned to Me” view. Each item includes a thumbnail, inferred attributes (type, material/finish, condition indicators, brand/model), a confidence score, and the source site context. Users can jump to a detailed item view from the queue.

Goals:
- Enable reviewers to quickly triage low-confidence detections, correct or confirm AI results, flag exceptions, and merge or flag duplicates.
- Provide bulk operations to accelerate reviews (e.g., accept all above a confidence threshold within the selected set, assign multiple items, export selections).
- Assign items to reviewers or teams with SLA notes and visibility into each reviewer’s workload.
- Present productivity metrics for reviewers (items reviewed per hour, average review time) to drive efficiency and accountability.
- Ensure a consistent, responsive UX across devices, with enterprise-grade validation, audit trails, and exports.

Connected features:
- Audit items with confidence scores, evidence (cropped detections + source image), and review decisions.
- Assignment and SLA tracking for review tasks.
- Bulk actions and export capabilities to CSV/PDF suitable for procurement and facilities workflows.
- Activity/audit log integration for traceability.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Queue Tabs: Low Confidence, Exceptions, Duplicates, Assigned to Me
- Item Cards List: Each card shows thumbnail, inferred attributes, confidence, site context, and a jump-to-detail CTA
- Bulk Operations: Actions like “Accept below threshold,” “Assign,” and “Export selection”
- Assignment Panel: Choose assignee (individual or team), SLA notes, and due dates
- Reviewer Metrics: KPIs such as items reviewed per hour and average review time
- Visual treatment uses the provided color palette and typography guidelines, with focus on green accent for actions, white/light surfaces for cards, and strong black navigation/summary panels

API integrations:
- No external APIs connected in this task’s scope. Data should be handled via internal project APIs or mocked endpoints, ensuring proper data validation and null-safety.

## Components to Build
- ReviewQueuePage
  - Layout: Tabbed navigation, left rail (filters/summary), main content grid/list
  - State: activeTab, filters, selectedItems, bulkActionState, loading, error
- ItemCard
  - Props: item object (confidence, type, attributes, siteContext, imageUrl, evidenceUrls, status, assignedTo, etc.)
  - Behavior: onSelect, onJumpToDetail, hover states
- BulkActionsBar
  - Props: selectedItems, onAccept, onAssign, onExport
  - UI: Checkbox selection, bulk action buttons, progress indicators
- AssignmentPanel
  - Props: currentSelection, onAssignChange, onSubmitAssignment, slaNotes
  - UI: dropdowns for assignee (user/team), SLA text area, due date (optional), confirm button
- FiltersPanel
  - Props: availableFilters, activeFilters, onFilterChange
  - UI: multi-selects, range sliders for confidence, site/location filters, status toggles
- MetricsPanel
  - Props: metricsData
  - UI: key metrics cards (items per hour, avg review time, total items, etc.)
- ItemDetailLink
  - Small utility component to navigate to a detailed audit item view
- DataAdapter / Hooks
  - useReviewQueueData: fetch queue data, apply client-side guards, expose data safely
  - useBulkExport: prepare and trigger export (CSV/PDF) with proper null-safe handling
- Validation & Utils
  - sanitizeItem(item): returns a safe shape with defaults
  - ensureArray(data): returns Array.isArray(data) ? data : []
  - safeMap(data, fn): (ensureArray(data)).map(fn)
  - formatConfidence(conf): string with percent
  - toDateString(ts): formatted date
- Accessibility
  - Keyboard navigable, aria-labels, role="button" on clickable items
  - High-contrast focus outlines
- Tests (Suggested)
  - Unit tests for safe array operations, data guards
  - Tests for bulk actions with empty selections
  - Tests for assignment panel validation
  - Tests for filtering edge cases (no results)

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Tech stack: React (with TypeScript), Vite/Next.js, Recoil/Redux or Context for state, React Query or SWR for data fetching (internal APIs).
- State initialization and typing:
  - useState<T[]>([]) for all arrays (e.g., const [selectedItems, setSelectedItems] = useState<string[]>([]))
  - All data fetch results must be guarded using data ?? [] and Array.isArray checks
- Data handling and safety:
  - Always use: const items = Array.isArray(data?.items) ? data.items : []
  - When deriving derived data from API responses, use destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], total = 0 } = response ?? {}
  - Guard all map/filter/reduce usage: (items ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- UI behavior:
  - Tabs switch should trigger a data fetch with the correct tab parameter
  - Each ItemCard shows confidence, site context, and a CTA to go to detail
  - Bulk actions disabled when no items selected
  - Assignment panel validates assignee selection and SLA notes before enabling submit
  - Filters should support multi-select, range filters, and clear all
- Performance:
  - Lazy load items as user scrolls if the queue can be large
  - Debounced filter inputs to avoid excessive fetches
- Visual consistency:
  - Adhere to the provided color palette and typography
  - Card layout with 16–24px radius, subtle shadows
  - Hover/active states emphasize selected items with the accent green
- Security considerations:
  - Do not reveal internal identifiers in UI where not needed
  - Ensure any export data does not leak sensitive fields unless allowed by policy

### Backend
- Data model to support:
  - ReviewItem: id, aiItemId, type, attributes, confidence, siteContext, imageUrl, evidenceUrls[], status (lowConfidence, exception, duplicate, approved, inReview), assignedTo, reviewerNotes, createdAt, updatedAt
  - Assignment: id, reviewerId, teamId, slaNotes, dueDate, createdAt
  - ReviewLog: id, itemId, action, actorId, timestamp, details
  - Export: id, type (csv/pdf), generatedAt, fileUrl
- API endpoints (internal):
  - GET /api/review-queue?tab=low|exceptions|duplicates&filters=...&page=1&pageSize=50
  - POST /api/review-queue/select (payload: { itemIds: string[] })
  - POST /api/review-queue/assign (payload: { itemIds: string[], assigneeId, teamId, slaNotes, dueDate })
  - POST /api/review-queue/bulk-accept (payload: { itemIds: string[], action: 'accept'|'flag' })
  - POST /api/review-queue/export (payload: { itemIds: string[], format: 'csv'|'pdf' })
  - GET /api/review-queue/metrics (returns itemsPerHour, avgReviewTime, totalReviewed)
- Database considerations:
  - Indexes on item status, assignedTo, confidence, and site context
  - Audit logs for every review action
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation for required fields in assignment and bulk actions
  - Return consistent error shapes with safe defaults

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - ReviewQueuePage calls useReviewQueueData to fetch based on active tab and filters
  - ItemCard renders item metadata derived safely from API response
  - BulkActionsBar triggers assignment and acceptance endpoints; on success, refresh the queue and update metrics
  - AssignmentPanel posts to /assign; on success, updates UI and logs SLA notes
  - MetricsPanel fetches through /metrics to display reviewer productivity
- Data safety:
  - All API data must be guarded with data ?? [] and Array.isArray checks
  - No direct access to potentially null fields without defaults
- State synchronization:
  - Optimistic UI updates can be used cautiously; always verify with the server response
  - Ensure bulk operations handle partial failures gracefully with per-item status feedback

## User Experience Flow
1) User lands on Review Queue
- The page loads with a default tab (Low Confidence) and an initial dataset.
- Metrics panel shows current productivity stats.
- Filters are available to narrow results.

2) Review items
- User scans item cards, reviews thumbnails and inferred attributes, and uses Jump to Detail to open an item.
- User marks items or approves directly via bulk actions.

3) Bulk actions
- User selects multiple items via checkboxes.
- Bulk bar enables actions: Accept below threshold, Assign, Export
- On Assign: AssignmentPanel opens; user selects assignee (user/team), adds SLA notes, optional due date, and submits.
- On Accept: Server processes per-item decisions; UI updates with new statuses and removes items from queue as appropriate.

4) Assignments and SLA tracking
- Assigned items show in Assigned to Me tab and in the assignee’s workload.
- SLA notes are persisted with the assignment and visible in item detail and logs.

5) Review productivity
- Metrics panel updates in real-time or on demand, showing items reviewed per hour and average review time.

6) Exports
- User exports selected items to CSV/PDF; a download link is provided and the export is logged.

7) Edge cases
- Empty results: UI shows empty state with guidance to adjust filters.
- No selection for bulk actions: UI disables bulk buttons and provides hints.
- API errors: Graceful error messaging and retry options.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models: 
  - ReviewItem {
      id: string
      aiItemId: string
      type: string
      attributes: Record<string, any>
      confidence: number
      siteContext: { clientId?: string; siteId?: string; location?: string }
      imageUrl?: string
      evidenceUrls?: string[]
      status: 'lowConfidence' | 'exception' | 'duplicate' | 'inReview' | 'approved'
      assignedTo?: string
      reviewerNotes?: string
      createdAt: string
      updatedAt: string
    }
  - Assignment {
      id: string
      itemIds: string[]
      assigneeId: string
      teamId?: string
      slaNotes?: string
      dueDate?: string
      createdAt: string
      updatedAt: string
    }
  - ReviewLog {
      id: string
      itemId: string
      action: string
      actorId: string
      timestamp: string
      details?: string
    }

- API Endpoints:
  - GET /api/review-queue?tab={low|exceptions|duplicates|assigned}&filters={...}&page={n}&pageSize={m}
  - POST /api/review-queue/select { itemIds: string[] }
  - POST /api/review-queue/assign { itemIds: string[], assigneeId, teamId, slaNotes, dueDate }
  - POST /api/review-queue/bulk-accept { itemIds: string[], action: 'accept'|'flag' }
  - POST /api/review-queue/export { itemIds: string[], format: 'csv'|'pdf' }
  - GET /api/review-queue/metrics

- Security:
  - JWT/SSO integration for authentication and authorization
  - RBAC: roles for reviewer, team lead, admin
  - Tenant isolation for enterprise clients
  - Audit logs for actions (who did what when)

- Validation:
  - Client-side: required fields, type checks, and guards for arrays
  - Server-side: strict validation with explicit error messages; ensure inputs are sanitized before persistence

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Review Queue page renders with four tabs: Low Confidence, Exceptions, Duplicates, Assigned to Me
- [ ] Data fetch safely handles null results and uses Array.isArray guards; no runtime errors due to undefined arrays
- [ ] All array operations are guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) and similar patterns
- [ ] User can select multiple items and trigger bulk actions; bulk actions are disabled when no selection
- [ ] Assignment panel validates assignee and SLA notes before enabling submit; on success, items are reassigned and UI updates
- [ ] Export functionality returns a downloadable file and logs the export
- [ ] Metrics panel displays items reviewed per hour and average review time with correct defaults when data is missing
- [ ] All UI adheres to the provided color palette, typography, and spacing guidelines
- [ ] Comprehensive unit tests cover safe data handling, bulk actions, and assignment validation
- [ ] Accessibility requirements are met (keyboard navigation, aria labels, focus states)

